ldquo;Hey,rdquo; she says again.nbsp; He drops his coat onto the chair and moves into the kitchen to get a soda.nbsp; She picks up the remote and begins flipping rapidly through the channels, then turns the set off again.nbsp; Eventually he leaves the can on the counter and comes back into the living room, sitting down on the coffee table across from her and taking her hands.

ldquo;Maggie, look at me.rdquo; She does--or, at least, as well as shersquo;s able to at this point.

ldquo;Irsquo;m only going to say this once.nbsp; Yoursquo;re welcome to crash here, but yoursquo;re not getting a fix.nbsp; I wonrsquo;t have that in my house.nbsp; You understand?rdquo;

